==English==

===Etymology===
From {{prefix|re|live|lang=en}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ɹiːˈlɪv/|lang=en}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|reliv}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[experience]] (something) again; to live over again. {{defdate|from 18th c.}}
#: ''I '''relive''' that horrible accident every night and wake screaming.''
# {{lb|en|obsolete|transitive}} To bring back to life; to [[revive]], [[resuscitate]]. {{defdate|16th-17th c.}}
#* '''1590''', {{w|Edmund Spenser}}, ''The Faerie Queene'', III.4:
#*: Had she not beene devoide of mortall slime, / Shee should not then have bene '''relyv'd''' againe [...].
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To come back to life.

